# wasm4pm TPOT2 Search Space

> Auto-generated by `ggen sync` from `queries/extract-operators.rq`. Do not edit by hand.

This report enumerates the wasm4pm process-mining algorithm registry recast as a
TPOT2-style genetic-programming search space. Each of the 9 pipeline stages
corresponds to one wasm4pm `pi:category`; each algorithm within a category becomes
a candidate **operator** at that stage. TPOT2's `config_dict` is the set of all
operators below; its NSGA-II multi-objective optimizer maximizes `quality` and
minimizes `cost` (speed tier). We mirror that with the SPARQL-derived fitness
score `fitness = quality_tier - (0.5 * speed_tier)` (lambda_cost = 0.5). The
**elite?** column marks the per-stage argmax-fitness operator that the
auto-configured pipeline selects.

